<br>
Does no one realise the value of stat food?  No one is willing to pay for food?<br>
<br>
Oh I've heard the arguements:<br>
<br>
&quot;It's too hard!&quot;<br>
<br>
Put the food in your top inventory slot.  It's that easy.  If you need to have different food for different purposes just switch it around the same way you switch gear for raids or for tradeskilling.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'll eat it!&quot;<br>
<br>
So?  Even if you can never remember to force feed the new foods are still usually worth it.  Let me ask you this?<br>
If there were a buff that gave you 5 stamina, 5 agility, 5 dexterity and 30 hit points, could NEVER be dispelled and lasted THIRTY HOURS would you pay 200pp to get it?  I'd say that was a bargain.  Well that's a Halas 10lb Meat pie.  And you can extend the duration by occasionally trying to remember to force feed something.<br>
<br>
If you could have 5 to all resists for the duration of a raid (say 12 hours) what would you pay?  A fiar amount I'd guess.  Holy Cakes add +5 to all resists and I'm sure they'll be selling for about 50pp each.<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know where to buy it.&quot;<br>
<br>
Check The Bazaar or the Market channel.  Or make friends with a baker.  Or send ME a tell for Karana's sake!<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm new, I can't affford 10pp let alone 100!&quot;  <br>
<br>
There are foods that add statistics that can be purchased for about the same price as rations.  Ohabah Truffles (+6 AGI, +6 Dex, -1 WIS, -1 INT) are going for 35pp as stack (1.5 pp each) and there's a LOT cheaper than that.  Bakers will probably take custom orders if you ask nicely.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm a bard I don't need to eat if I don't want to.&quot;<br>
<br>
Perfect!  You won't consume that expensive food then will you?<br>
<br>
&quot;Baking used to be the only purely for fun trade skill.  It's gauche that people are trying to make money from it now.&quot;<br>
<br>
Actually Brewing used to be far more for fun than Baking.  And guess what?  They've made drinks with incredibly impressive stats as well.  Verant has decided to let all traders recoup thier high investment.  Please help tradeskillers and yourself by becoming familiar with how everything works.<br>
<br>
&quot;DUDE you Su&gt;&lt;&gt;&lt;0r!  I have phat lewt!  I 0wn your AZZ!  I need 0 frum ju!&quot;<br>
<br>
Please go away.<br>
<br>
So, in closing, support the local Baking and Brewing industries.<br>
